abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's doctor has proclaimed him "a 77-year-old man in outstanding health," according to a letter released by his campaign on Thursday.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's doctor has proclaimed him "a 77-year-old man in outstanding health," according to a letter released by his campaign on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg's doctor has proclaimed him "a 77-year-old man in outstanding health," according to a letter released by his campaign on Thursday.
headline_main: Democratic Presidential Candidate Bloomberg in 'Outstanding Health': Doctor
headline_print_headline: Democratic Presidential Candidate Bloomberg in 'Outstanding Health': Doctor

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday signed off on a trade deal with China that would delay a new round of tariffs that was to be put in place on Dec. 15, Bloomberg News reported.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday signed off on a trade deal with China that would delay a new round of tariffs that was to be put in place on Dec. 15, Bloomberg News reported.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday signed off on a trade deal with China that would delay a new round of tariffs that was to be put in place on Dec. 15, Bloomberg News reported.
headline_main: Trump Signs Off on Tariff Deal With China: Bloomberg News
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Off on Tariff Deal With China: Bloomberg News

abstract: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
snippet: Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Public testimony in Congress has done little to sway Wisconsin voters' views on the possible impeachment of President Donald Trump, a new poll from the battleground state showed on Thursday.
headline_main: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters
headline_print_headline: Poll Shows Impeachment Hearings Had Little Sway on Wisconsin Voters

abstract: A court in Monaco has dismissed a case in which a prominent European art dealer was accused by a Russian oligarch who lived in the principality of fraud and money laundering, a prosecutor has confirmed.
snippet: A court in Monaco has dismissed a case in which a prominent European art dealer was accused by a Russian oligarch who lived in the principality of fraud and money laundering, a prosecutor has confirmed.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - A court in Monaco has dismissed a case in which a prominent European art dealer was accused by a Russian oligarch who lived in the principality of fraud and money laundering, a prosecutor has confirmed.
headline_main: Monaco Court Dismisses Case Against Art Dealer Accused of Defrauding Russian Oligarch
headline_print_headline: Monaco Court Dismisses Case Against Art Dealer Accused of Defrauding Russian Oligarch

abstract: The president’s concern is not so much whom he will be debating but the commission that runs the debates.
snippet: The president’s concern is not so much whom he will be debating but the commission that runs the debates.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is discussing with his advisers the possibility of sitting out the general election debates in 2020 because of his misgivings about the commission that oversees them, according to two people familiar with the discussions.

abstract: A U.S. labor board on Thursday approved McDonald's Corp's proposed settlement allowing the fast-food company to avoid a ruling on whether it is a “joint employer” of franchise workers and could be made to bargain with unions.
snippet: A U.S. labor board on Thursday approved McDonald's Corp's proposed settlement allowing the fast-food company to avoid a ruling on whether it is a “joint employer” of franchise workers and could be made to bargain with unions.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - A U.S. labor board on Thursday approved McDonald's Corp's proposed settlement allowing the fast-food company to avoid a ruling on whether it is a “joint employer” of franchise workers and could be made to bargain with unions.
headline_main: U.S. Labor Board Approves McDonald's Bid to Settle Case by Franchise Workers
headline_print_headline: U.S. Labor Board Approves McDonald's Bid to Settle Case by Franchise Workers

abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday signed off on a trade deal with China that would delay a new round of tariffs that was to be put in place on Dec. 15, Bloomberg News reported.
snippet: U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday signed off on a trade deal with China that would delay a new round of tariffs that was to be put in place on Dec. 15, Bloomberg News reported.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — U.S. President Donald Trump on Thursday signed off on a trade deal with China that would delay a new round of tariffs that was to be put in place on Dec. 15, Bloomberg News reported.
headline_main: Trump Signs Off on Tariff Deal With China-Bloomberg News
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs Off on Tariff Deal With China-Bloomberg News

abstract: Republican climate denial is even scarier than Trumpism.
snippet: Republican climate denial is even scarier than Trumpism.
lead_paragraph: The most terrifying aspect of the U.S. political drama isn’t the revelation that the president has abused his power for personal gain. If you didn’t see that coming from the day Donald Trump was elected, you weren’t paying attention.
